com.joliciel.talismane.parser

Class ParseConfiguration

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.joliciel.talismane.parser.ParseConfiguration
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ClassificationSolution, HasFeatureCache, Solution, ParseConfigurationWrapper, java.lang.Comparable<ParseConfiguration>

    public final class ParseConfiguration
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<ParseConfiguration>, ClassificationSolution, ParseConfigurationWrapper, HasFeatureCache
    A sequence of dependency arcs applied to a given sequence of pos-tagged tokens, as well as the stack and buffer indicating the pos-tagged tokens already visited and not yet visited.
    Author:
    Assaf Urieli

      • addManualNonProjectiveDependency

        public DependencyArc addManualNonProjectiveDependency(PosTaggedToken head,
                                                      PosTaggedToken dependent,
                                                      java.lang.String label)
                                               throws CircularDependencyException
        Add the given dependency to the current configuration's non-projective dependency set. This should only be used when reading a previously annotated corpus, to indicate the projective and non-projective governor for a given token. If the transition system is capable of producing its own non-projective dependencies there should be no need to distinguish between projective and non-projective.
        Throws:
        CircularDependencyException - if this would create a circular dependency

      • isUseGeometricMeanForProbs

        public boolean isUseGeometricMeanForProbs()
        True: use a geometric mean when calculating individual arc probabilities (which multiply the probabilities for the transitions since the last arc was added). False: use the simple product. Default is true.
